title: Relativity launches first Terran 1
summary: Relativity Space’s first Terran 1 rocket successfully got off the launch pad March 22 but failed to reach orbit because of an upper stage malfunction.

title: Relativity’s first 3D-printed rocket launches successfully but fails to reach orbit
summary: Relativity Space, a 3D-printing specialist, launched the inaugural flight of its Terran 1 rocket late on Wednesday night, which successfully met some mission objectives before failing to reach orbit.

title: Relativity Makes History With Maiden Terran 1 Flight, Fails To Reach Orbit
summary: Relativity Space has made history successfully launching its Terran 1 launch vehicle for the first time.

title: SpaceX Starlink V2 Satellites Experiencing Problems On Orbit
summary: SpaceX may need to deorbit some of the first batch of larger second-generation Starlink satellites due to issues they are currently facing.

title: SpaceX experiencing problems with first upgraded Starlink V2 satellites
summary: The first set of larger second-generation Starlink satellites is experiencing problems that could require SpaceX to deorbit at least some of them.

title: Avio secures Italian government funding for methane engine and small launch vehicle prototype
summary: Avio is moving ahead with efforts to develop a larger methane-fueled rocket engine and a prototype small launch vehicle with more than $300 million in funding from the Italian government.

title: NRO Signs 5 Year Commercial Hyperspectral Satellite Imagery Agreement
summary: The National Reconnaissance Office (NRO) has entered into five-year agreements with six commercial providers of hyperspectral satellite imagery.

title: USSF Requests First Tactically Responsive Space Program Budget
summary: The U.S. Space Force has requested $60 million over the next two years from Congress for a program called tactically responsive space, according to budget documents submitted last week.

title: Innospace Test Launches HANBIT-TLV From Brazil Successfully
summary: South Korean rocket startup Innospace has successfully launching its HANBIT-TLV suborbital rocket from Brazil's Alcântara Space Center for the first time.
